{
  "text": "These findings suggest that the mechanical and thermal hypersensitivity that we documented after ION-CCI may be associated with hyperexcitability of injured myelinated or unmyelinated ION primary afferent fibers. It is noteworthy that the heat and mechanical hypersensitivity lasted for at least 21 days after the ION-CCI, whereas cold hypersensitivity lasted for 14 days after ION-CCI. It is possible that the different time-courses in nocifensive behaviors between mechanical or heat hypersensitivity and cold hypersensitivity in the ION-CCI rats may be due, at least in part, to different effects of ION-CCI on mechanical or heat sensitive primary afferent fibers versus cold-sensitive fibers, such as channel or receptor expression in each type of primary afferent neurons after the CCI [CITATION_1] .",
